~ Protein rich Poha bites ~

Detailed recipe for Protein rich Poha Bites -
Ingredients -
1. Poha - 1/2 cup
2. Yellow moong daal - 1/2 cup
3. Dahi - 1/2 cup
4. Salt - 1 1/2 tsp ( as per taste)
5. Turmeric - a pinch of 
6. Ginger green chilli paste - 1 tsp
7. Veggies - beetroot - 1 medium 
  Carrot - 1 medium
  Beans - 3-4 
  Peas - 1/4 cup
8. Oil - 2 tsp (for greasing & tempering)
9. Rai - 1/2 tsp
10. White sesame seeds - 1 tsp
11. Curry leaves - 1 sprig
12. Bhuna jeera masala or chaat masala - a pinch of 
13. Black pepper powder - 1/4 tsp (optional) 

Method - 
1. Grind poha & moong daal together. 
2. Add dahi into it & mix it well. Don’t add too much of water. Cover the mixture & let it rest for half an hour.
3. meanwhile steam cook all the veggies as per choice - I took carrot, beetroot, beans & green peas (which I froze in peak season)
4. Once they are soft & mushy, grind them roughly or if you want chunks you can grind it finely too.
5. Add this grind veggies to poha daal mixture.
6. Now add a tsp of ginger green chilli paste, salt & turmeric.
7. If you want you can add some black pepper powder too as per taste you require.
8. Mix this all very well & make small balls greasing your palms.
9. Put those balls on a greased tray & steam cook for 10-14 mins. 
10. For the tempering add oil in a pan, put rai, sesame seeds & curry leaves.
11. Put all the balls & sprinkle jeera masala on top of it. 
12. Serve hot with raw mango-pudina chutney or ketchup & enjoy 😊

Save it so you miss it later 😊

Blue tea ~
As the most hectic day of week ends..it's time to calm your mind & detox your body..& apart from Blue Tea, no one else can do both these things.

So, stop & take a sip of this beautiful Blue tea & see the color changing from 💙 -> 💜with every drop of lime 🍋

Blue tea, also known as butterfly pea tea has numerous health benefits..Here are some reasons why you might consider drinking blue tea:

1. Antioxidant properties: Blue tea contains antioxidants that can help protect the body against free radicals and oxidative stress.

2. Anti-inflammatory properties: Blue tea may help reduce inflammation and improve overall health.

3. Brain health: The tea contains compounds that may improve memory and cognitive function.

4. Weight loss: Some studies suggest that blue tea may aid in weight loss by boosting metabolism.

5. Immune system support: Blue tea is believed to have immunomodulatory effects.

6. Digestive health: Blue tea may help soothe digestive issues.

7. Skin and hair benefits: Antioxidants in blue tea may promote healthy skin and hair.

8. Low caffeine: Blue tea is naturally caffeine-free.

9. Stress relief: The tea's calming effects may help reduce stress.

10. Unique taste: Blue tea has a subtle floral flavor.

To make blue tea, steep dried butterfly pea flowers in hot water. You can add honey or lemon to taste.

Healthy breakfast Series Ep 11 ~ Ragi Masoor Daal Idli ~

Detailed Recipe for Ragi Masur Daal ki Idli :
Ingredients-
1. Ragi - 1/2 cup
2. Masur Daal - 1/2 cup
3. Urad Daal - 1/2 cup
4. Methi - 1/2 tsp
5. Salt - 1 tsp
For moongfali ki chutney-
6. Peanuts(moongfali) - 1/2 cup
7. Dhaniya - handful
8. ginger - 1 "
9. green chilli - 2 small
10. dahi - 2 tbsp
For tadka -
11. Rai - 1/2 tsp
12. Curry leaves - 5-6
13. hing - a pinch
14. Oil - 1 tsp
15. dry red chilli 1 (optional)
Method -
1. Wash & soak Ragi, Masur Daal, urad daal & methi for 4-5 hrs.
2. Grind fine using little water.
3. Pour the batter in big bowl & add Salt.
4. Mix nicely, cover & keep it at warm place to ferment for 6-8 hrs or overnight.
5. Once fermented mix the batter & pour it in greased idli mould.
6. Steam cook for 10-12 mins on high flame.
7. Once done, let it cool a bit then De-mould idlis.
For moongfali ki chutney :
8. Dry roast moongfali & let it cool.
9. Grind in paste adding Salt, Ginger, green chilli, coriander & curd.
10. Prepare tadka adding hing, Rai, curry leaves in hot oil. Add it to chutney.
Now enjoy this wonderful Ragi masoor daal idli with moongfali ki chutney & don't compromise with you taste in your weight loss journey..
& Don't forget to check more tasty recipes at this page that will help you in weight loss 😊😊

~ Corn Cheese Buns ~

Detailed recipe for Corn cheese bun -
1. Whole wheat flour - 1.5 cups
2. Milk powder - 1/2 cup
3. Warm water - 3/4 cup
4. Sugar - 1 tbsp
5. Activated dry yeast - 1 tbsp
6. Salt - a pinch of 
7. Oil - 1/4 cup + 1 tbsp
8. Warm milk - 2 tbsp
9. For stuffing - chopped onions - 1/4 cup
10.  Boiled corn - 1/4 cup
11.  Capsicum - 1/4 cup
12.  Paneer - 1/4 cup (in small cubes)
13.  Mozzarella cheese - 1/2 cup
14.  Salt - 1/2 tsp
15.  Oregano - 1 tsp
16.  Chilli flakes - 1 tsp
17.  Ketchup - 1 tbsp
18. White & black sesame seeds -  1+1 tsp
19. Butter - 1 tbsp

Method -
1. Take warm water in a bowl & add activated dry yeast with sugar.
2. Cover the bowl & let the yeast activate for 10 mins.
3. Sieve whole wheat flour, mix milk powder & salt.
4. Add activated yeast mixture & prepare a dough. 
5. Buns or breads made with whole wheat flour needs a little more kneading this make the dough soft & rises well.. so knead the dough for 7-8 mins using little warm milk gradually & some oil (if requires).
6. Keep it in big greased bowl for 2 hrs to proof at some warm place.
7. Meanwhile prepare the stuffing by sautéing veggies - onion, capsicum, corn & paneer in a tsp of oil.
8. Add salt, oregano, chilli flakes & a tbsp of ketchup at the last. Mex everything well.
9. Once the stuffing gets at room temperature add chopped/grated mozzarella cheese & mix nicely.
10. When the dough is risen divide it into equal parts (I made 8 buns)
11. Fill the prepared stuffing & make small buns of all.
12. Keep it in a baking tray - covered for 2nd proofing about 30 mins. 
13. Now brush some milk & sprinkle sesame seeds on top.
14. Bake it for 30 mins at 160 degrees or in kadai at lowest flame for 40-45 mins, till it gets golden on top.
15. When the buns are baked, brush some butter & cover it with kitchen towel for 10 mins - this keeps the buns soft & moist. Now enjoy 😊

Seeds Cracker ~

Detailed recipe for Seed Cracker -
Ingredients - 
1. Flax seeds - 1/2 cup
2. Pumpkin seeds - 1/2 cup
3. Chia seeds - 1/2 cup
4. Musk Melon seeds - 1/4 cup
5. White sesame seeds - 1/4 cup
6. Psyllium husk - 1/4 cup
7. Salt - 1 tsp (you may increase it as per taste)
8. Oregano - 1 tsp 
9. Chilli flakes - 1 tsp
10. Hot Water - 3/4 cup
11. Oil / ghee for greasing

Method - 
1. Put all the seeds in a bowl along with psyllium husk, salt , oregano & chilli flakes.
2. Mix everything well & add hot water.
3. Mix it & keep it covered for half an hour.
4. Now take a baking tray -  lined & greased.
5. Spread thin layer of seed mix & bake it for 1 hr on 150 degrees. 
6. Let them cool down completely. 
7. Remove baking sheet carefully & store it in air tight jar.

For High Protein Mint spread -
Ingredients - 
1. Paneer - 50 gms
2. Mint leaves - 10-12
3. Garlic - 2 
4. Green chilli - 1 small
5. Blak pepper - 2-3 pcs
6. Salt - 1/2 tsp
7. Water - 2-3 tbsp (as required)

Method -
1. Put everything in grinder & grind it till you get smooth paste.
2. You can store it in refrigerator for 2 days..not more than that.

~ Bael sharbat ~

There are some recipes which are close to your heart because they are connected with your childhood.
For me Bael Shabbat holds a special place in my memories…because every time when I make it for my kids, I remember how my grandfather use to make this & me sitting at one side closely watch him mashing the pulp & removing all the roughages.

🍃Bael ka sharbat is well-known for its positive effects on the digestive system & is very good for constipation.
🍃Bael sharbat has natural cooling properties, making it an ideal beverage to beat the summer heat and prevent heat-related issues like heatstroke.
🍃This juice acts as a natural detoxifier, aiding in flushing out toxins from the body and supporting liver health.

Episode 10 of Breakfast Series: Moong Appe! 

Detailed recipe for Moong Appe -
Ingredients - made 24-25 appe 
1. Soaked moong bean - 1 1/2 cup 
2. Sooji (semolina) - 1/2 cup
3. Ginger - 1”
4. Green chilli - 1-2
5. Jeera - 1tsp
6. Salt - 1 tsp
7. Paneer - 50 gms
8. Coriander - a bunch of 
9. Veggies as per choice (you can add any veggies)
* Onion
* Capsicum
* Bell peppers
* Carrot
10. Baking soda or fruit salt - 1/2 tsp
11. Oil or ghee 

Method - 
1. Soak moong for 4-5 hrs or overnight.
2. Grind moong with ginger, green chilli, coriander & some water.
3. Put the batter in the bowl & add sooji. Cover it & let it rest for 7-8 mins.
4. Chop all the veggies as per choice.
5. Add them in the moong & sooji batter. 
6. Add jeera & salt . & add baking soda or fruit salt .  Mix well.
7. Cut the paneer in small cubes. 
8. Grease appe/ paniyaram pan & half fill with the mixture. Put paneer cubes into it & top it up with mixture.
9. Cook covered for 5-7 mins & flip them. 
10. cook till golden brown & crisp and enjoy hot.
